{"id":"physics/9803013","submitter":"Champneys Ar.","authors":"Alan R Champneys (1) Boris A Malomed (2) Mark J friedman (3) ((1)\n  University of Bristol, (2) Tel Aviv University, (3) University of Alabama)","title":"Thirring Solitons in the presence of dispersion","comments":"12 pages, Latex. To appear in Phys. Rev. Lett","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.Lett. 80 (1998) 4169-4172","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.80.4169","report-no":"ANM-97-12","categories":"physics.optics","license":null,"abstract":"  The effect of dispersion or diffraction on zero-velocity solitons is studied\nfor the generalized massive Thirring model describing a nonlinear optical fiber\nwith grating or parallel-coupled planar waveguides with misaligned axes. The\nThirring solitons existing at zero dispersion/diffraction are shown numerically\nto be separated by a finite gap from three isolated soliton branches. Inside\nthe gap, there is an infinity of multi-soliton branches. Thus, the Thirring\nsolitons are structurally unstable. In another parameter region (far from the\nThirring limit), solitons exist everywhere.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 1998 13:58:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
